---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Fractune · Field instrument for architectural fluency">
  <SiteHeader />

  <!-- ─── Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ft-hero">
    <div class="ft-grid">
      <aside class="ft-spine">
        <div class="ft-spine-block">
          <div class="ft-spine-section">A.01 STATEMENT</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ft-spine-block">
          <div class="ft-spine-heading">INSTRUMENT</div>
          <div>Fractune v2.0</div>
          <div>iOS 26.4+</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ft-spine-block">
          <div class="ft-spine-heading">MEASURES</div>
          <div>Architectural Fluency F</div>
          <div>F ∈ [0, 1]</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ft-spine-block">
          <div class="ft-spine-heading">METHOD</div>
          <div>Four-dimensional</div>
          <div>Edge · Spectral · Colour</div>
          <div>On-device</div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="ft-hero-statement">
        <h1 class="ft-h1">
          Some buildings<br />
          feel right.<br />
          <span class="ft-h1-accent">Now you can</span><br />
          <span class="ft-h1-accent">measure why.</span>
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Specimen photograph, hero asset has the iPhone composited in
         and the phone deliberately overhangs the photo top + bottom -->
    <figure class="ft-hero-figure">
      <div class="ft-photo-frame">
        <img src="/mockups/hero2.png" alt="Brick facade in Venice with Fractune showing F ≈ 0.77 for the facade" class="ft-photo-img" loading="eager" />

        <!-- Corner ticks, the instrument is sighted on the facade -->
        <span class="ft-tick ft-tick-tl"></span>
        <span class="ft-tick ft-tick-tr"></span>
        <span class="ft-tick ft-tick-bl"></span>
        <span class="ft-tick ft-tick-br"></span>

        <!-- Specimen annotation -->
        <div class="ft-specimen">
          <div class="ft-specimen-id">SPECIMEN · SS-047</div>
          <div>Campo San Marziale</div>
          <div>Venezia, IT · 2025.09</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <figcaption class="ft-photo-caption">
        <span>PL. 01 · BRICK FACADE · VENEZIA · F · N = 85 REFERENCE</span>
        <span>PHOTO · FRACTUNE FIELD ARCHIVE</span>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <!-- Descriptor + CTA + Stats -->
    <div class="ft-hero-bottom">
      <div class="ft-grid">
        <aside class="ft-spine"></aside>
        <div class="ft-hero-bottom-content">
          <p class="ft-hero-descriptor">
            Fractune is a pocket-sized field instrument for reading the
            architectural fluency of building facades.
            <span class="ft-muted">
              Point, scan, and quantify the visual coherence a building
              places into the world, across four dimensions: fractal
              complexity, rhythm, colour, and structure.
            </span>
          </p>
          <div class="ft-cta-block">
            <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/fractune/idXXXXXXXXXX" class="ft-app-store-link" aria-label="Download Fractune on the App Store">
              <img src="/app-store-badge.svg" alt="Download on the App Store" class="ft-app-store-badge" />
            </a>
            <div class="ft-cta-req">REQ · IPHONE 14 OR LATER · iOS 26.4+</div>
            <div class="ft-stats">
              <div class="ft-stat">
                <div class="ft-stat-num">F</div>
                <div class="ft-stat-label">Headline metric</div>
              </div>
              <div class="ft-stat">
                <div class="ft-stat-num">4</div>
                <div class="ft-stat-label">Dimensions</div>
              </div>
              <div class="ft-stat">
                <div class="ft-stat-num">85</div>
                <div class="ft-stat-label">References</div>
              </div>
              <div class="ft-stat">
                <div class="ft-stat-num">0</div>
                <div class="ft-stat-label">Images leave device</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── §01, F and the four dimensions ─────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ft-section ft-bg-surface">
    <div class="ft-grid">
      <aside class="ft-spine">
        <div class="ft-spine-num">§ 01</div>
        <div>On the quantity</div>
        <div>F ∈ [0, 1]</div>
      </aside>
      <div class="ft-section-content">
        <h2 class="ft-h2">A composite reading made from four independent measurements.</h2>
        <div class="ft-two-col">
          <p>
            F is calibrated against six decades of empirical aesthetics
            research. Stamps' regression coefficient β = 0.72 for surface
            complexity, Spehar &amp; Taylor's 1/f<sup>1.2</sup> preference
            peak, Stanischewski et al.'s edge-orientation entropy, all
            converge on a sweet zone where well-composed facades cluster.
          </p>
          <p>
            The composition matters. A tile roof scores high on fractal
            dimension D alone, but its monotonous repetition fails on
            lacunarity Λ and edge-orientation entropy H<sub>θ</sub>. F
            catches this, the four dimensions correct each other.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- F-Scale figure -->
        <div class="ft-figure">
          <div class="ft-figure-header">
            <span>FIG. 01 · ARCHITECTURAL FLUENCY SCALE</span>
            <span>n = 85 reference buildings</span>
          </div>

          <div class="ft-fscale">
            <div class="ft-fscale-bar">
              <span class="ft-fscale-zone ft-fscale-monotone">MONOTONE</span>
              <span class="ft-fscale-zone ft-fscale-sweet">SWEET SPOT</span>
              <span class="ft-fscale-zone ft-fscale-chaos">NEAR CHAOS</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ft-fscale-ticks">
              <span class="ft-tick-0">0.0</span>
              <span class="ft-tick-55">0.55</span>
              <span class="ft-tick-75">0.75</span>
              <span class="ft-tick-100">1.0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ft-fscale-captions">
              <span>Plain glass wall</span>
              <span class="ft-fscale-sweet-text">Fluent · Coherent · Beloved buildings</span>
              <span>Visually overwhelming</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ft-fscale-mean">F · ICONIC MEAN</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ft-callouts">
          <div class="ft-callout ft-callout-sweet">
            <div class="ft-callout-label">SWEET SPOT · F = 0.55 – 0.75</div>
            <p>
              Where well-composed facades land. Renaissance palazzi,
              modernist Nordic vernacular, Belle Époque streets, different
              traditions, similar F.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-callout ft-callout-primary">
            <div class="ft-callout-label">FRACTAL SUB-DIMENSION · D = 1.41</div>
            <p>
              The Ostwald &amp; Vaughan mean across 85 canonical buildings.
              D is now one of four sub-scores feeding F, modulated by
              lacunarity Λ and edge-orientation entropy H<sub>θ</sub>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── §02, Three operations ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ft-section">
    <div class="ft-grid">
      <aside class="ft-spine">
        <div class="ft-spine-num">§ 02</div>
        <div>Three operations,</div>
        <div>no servers</div>
      </aside>
      <div class="ft-section-content">
        <h2 class="ft-h2">Point. Scan. Understand.</h2>
        <p class="ft-section-lead">
          Every step runs on the iPhone. No image leaves the device unless
          you choose to contribute the reading to the open dataset.
        </p>
        <div class="ft-ops">
          <div class="ft-op">
            <img
              src="/mockups/point.png"
              alt="CoreML segmentation isolating the facade with colored overlays"
              class="ft-op-phone"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="ft-op-label">OPERATION / 01</div>
            <div class="ft-op-title">Point</div>
            <p>Frame the facade. CoreML segmentation isolates the building surface from sky, vegetation, and street furniture.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-op">
            <img
              src="/mockups/scan.png"
              alt="Box-counting visualization, gold boxes covering the facade edges"
              class="ft-op-phone"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="ft-op-label">OPERATION / 02</div>
            <div class="ft-op-title">Scan</div>
            <p>Four parallel pipelines run on-device: fractal box-counting, FFT-based rhythm analysis, CIELAB colour clustering, and structural composition. F is composed from all four.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-op">
            <img
              src="/mockups/understand.png"
              alt="Result screen showing F with the sweet-spot bar and four dimension breakdown"
              class="ft-op-phone"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="ft-op-label">OPERATION / 03</div>
            <div class="ft-op-title">Understand</div>
            <p>F lands on the sweet-spot bar with confidence indicator. Fold open each dimension to see its sub-metrics: D, Λ, H<sub>θ</sub>, β, R<sub>w</sub>, B, V, Σ_h, κ, Δ_L.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── §03, Capabilities ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ft-section ft-bg-surface">
    <div class="ft-grid">
      <aside class="ft-spine ft-spine-with-phone">
        <div class="ft-spine-num">§ 03</div>
        <div>Seven capabilities,</div>
        <div>one scan</div>
        <figure class="ft-spine-phone">
          <img
            src="/mockups/instrument-in-full.png"
            alt="Fractune showing the full instrument with all four dimensions"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>PL. 03 · Instrument</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </aside>
      <div class="ft-section-content">
        <h2 class="ft-h2">The instrument in full.</h2>
        <p class="ft-section-lead">
          One measurement unfolds into seven parallel readings, geometry,
          rhythm, colour, structure, segmentation, history, and a calibrated
          uncertainty marker.
        </p>
        <div class="ft-features">
          <div class="ft-feature">
            <span class="ft-feature-num">01</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-title">Architectural Fluency F</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-body">A single composite score 0–1, calibrated to a sweet zone of 0.55–0.75.</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-tag">COMPOSITE</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-feature">
            <span class="ft-feature-num">02</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-title">Four Dimensions</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-body">Fractal, rhythm, colour, structure, each with its own sweet spot and breakdown.</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-tag">MULTI-DIM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-feature">
            <span class="ft-feature-num">03</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-title">CoreML Segmentation</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-body">On-device isolation of the facade from sky, vegetation, and surroundings.</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-tag">COREML</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-feature">
            <span class="ft-feature-num">04</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-title">Quality Confidence</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-body">F shown with "?" when image quality or perspective skew reduces reliability, never silently mislead.</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-tag">UNCERTAIN</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-feature">
            <span class="ft-feature-num">05</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-title">Session History</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-body">Every measurement saved with thumbnail and metadata, exportable as CSV.</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-tag">LOCAL</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-feature">
            <span class="ft-feature-num">06</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-title">Research Contribution</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-body">Anonymised scans optionally feed the open architectural dataset. Per-field consent.</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-tag">OPT-IN</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ft-feature">
            <span class="ft-feature-num">07</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-title">Home Screen Widget</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-body">Your latest F + D + C, plus pending donation queue, refreshed at a glance.</span>
            <span class="ft-feature-tag">WIDGETKIT</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── §04, Science ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ft-section">
    <div class="ft-grid">
      <aside class="ft-spine">
        <div class="ft-spine-num">§ 04</div>
        <div>Literature</div>
      </aside>
      <div class="ft-section-content ft-science-grid">
        <div>
          <h2 class="ft-h2">Built on decades of research.</h2>
          <p class="ft-science-lead">
            Box-counting methods in architecture date to Bovill (1996).
            Fractune extends the tradition with calibrated iPhone optics,
            on-device CoreML segmentation, FFT-based spectral rhythm
            analysis, and a four-dimensional composition framework drawing on
            Spehar, Stamps, Salingaros, Vartanian, and the Aarhus
            School-of-Architecture work on cognitive responses to space.
          </p>
          <a href="/science" class="ft-link-arrow">Read the full methodology →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="ft-references">
          <div class="ft-references-label">SELECTED REFERENCES</div>
          <div>Mandelbrot, B. (1982)</div>
          <div>Bovill, C. (1996)</div>
          <div>Stamps, A. E. (2000)</div>
          <div>Spehar &amp; Taylor (2003)</div>
          <div>Salingaros, N. (2006)</div>
          <div>Vartanian et al. (2013)</div>
          <div>Ostwald &amp; Vaughan (2016)</div>
          <div>Stanischewski et al. (2020)</div>
          <a href="/research" class="ft-references-link">and 44 others →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── §05, sites.fractune.dk ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ft-section ft-section-dark">
    <div class="ft-grid">
      <aside class="ft-spine ft-spine-dark">
        <div class="ft-spine-num">§ 05</div>
        <div>The atlas</div>
        <div>sites.fractune.dk</div>
      </aside>
      <div class="ft-section-content ft-atlas-grid">
        <div>
          <h2 class="ft-h2 ft-h2-light">Every reading lands<br />on a public map.</h2>
          <p class="ft-atlas-body">
            <strong>sites.fractune.dk</strong> is the browser-side companion
            to the app, a living atlas of anonymised facade readings. Filter
            by city, era, style, or F-band. Browse the sweet spot, hunt for
            outliers, compare your street to a Renaissance palazzo.
          </p>
          <div class="ft-atlas-stats">
            <div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-h">Browse</div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-b">Every reading, mapped and searchable.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-h">Compare</div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-b">Stack any two facades side by side.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-h">Filter</div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-b">By city, century, style, or F-band.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-h">Cite</div>
              <div class="ft-atlas-stat-b">Permalinks for every observation.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk" class="ft-link-arrow ft-link-arrow-light">Visit sites.fractune.dk →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Pre-composited laptop mockup of sites.fractune.dk -->
        <figure class="ft-atlas-laptop">
          <img
            src="/mockups/sites.png"
            alt="sites.fractune.dk showing analysed buildings on a satellite map of Europe"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>PL. 05 · sites.fractune.dk</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SiteFooter />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Grid ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .ft-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    max-width: 1168px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .ft-spine {
    padding-top: 6px;
  }
  .ft-spine-phone {
    display: block;
    margin: 32px 0 0;
  }
  .ft-spine-phone img {
    width: 140px;
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }
  .ft-spine-phone figcaption {
    margin-top: 10px;
    font-family: var(--ft-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--ft-text-dim);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .ft-spine-block { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .ft-spine-block:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .ft-spine-section,
  .ft-spine-heading,
  .ft-spine-num,
  .ft-spine div {
    font-family: var(--ft-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ft-text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .ft-spine-num {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ft-text);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .ft-spine-section,
  .ft-spine-heading {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ft-text);
  }

  /* ── Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .ft-hero { padding: 96px 64px 0; }
  .ft-hero-statement { padding-top: 0; }
  .ft-hero-statement .ft-h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans, 'Myriad Pro', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(56px, 7.2vw, 92px);
    line-height: 0.98;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 900px;
    color: var(--ft-text);
  }
  .ft-hero-statement .ft-h1-accent {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ft-primary);
  }

  /* Hero figure */
  .ft-hero-figure {
    margin: 72px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    position: relative;
  }
  .ft-photo-frame {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    /* The frame represents the visible Venice photo (16:9). The iPhone in
       hero2.png deliberately overhangs the photo top + bottom, so we let it
       spill out (no overflow:hidden) and reserve margin around it.
       Top overhang is small (~4.7% of frame height), bottom is ~7.5%. */
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    margin: 3% 0 7.5%;
    background: transparent;
  }
  .ft-photo-img {
    position: absolute;
    /* hero2.png photo region runs y=123..2711 of 2907. Pulling the image up
       by 4.73% of frame height aligns the photo top with the frame top. */
    top: -4.73%;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }
  .ft-tick {
    position: absolute;
    width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .ft-tick-tl { top: 24px; left: 24px; border-top: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); border-left: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }
  .ft-tick-tr { top: 24px; right: 24px; border-top: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); border-right: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }
  .ft-tick-bl { bottom: 24px; left: 24px; border-bottom: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); border-left: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }
  .ft-tick-br { bottom: 24px; right: 24px; border-bottom: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); border-right: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }

  .ft-specimen {
    position: absolute;
    top: 72px;
    left: 72px;
    font-family: var(--ft-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9);
    line-height: 1.9;
  }
  .ft-specimen-id { font-weight: 600; }

  /* iPhone bezel + screen */

  /* App Store badge */
  .ft-app-store-link {
    display: inline-block;
    line-height: 0;
  }
  .ft-app-store-badge {
    height: 52px;
    display: block;
  }

  .ft-photo-caption {
    max-width: 1168px;
    margin: 16px auto 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-family: var(--ft-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--ft-text-dim);
  }

  .ft-hero-bottom {
    padding: 80px 0 128px;
  }
  .ft-hero-bottom-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 1fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .ft-hero-descriptor {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--ft-text);
    line-height: 1.45;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .ft-muted { color: var(--ft-text-dim); }
  .ft-cta-block { padding-top: 6px; }
  .ft-cta-req {
    font-family: var(--ft-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--ft-text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin-top: 16px;
  }
  .ft-stats {
    margin-top: 40px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ft-border);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px 24px;
  }
  .ft-stat-num {
    font-family: var(--ft-mono);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 26px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ft-primary);
  }
  .ft-stat-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ft-text-dim);
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  /* ── Buttons ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .ft-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 14px 22px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 16px;
    transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .ft-btn-primary {
    background: var(--ft-primary);
    color: #fff;
  }
  .ft-btn-primary:hover { background: var(--ft-primary-hover); color: #fff; }

  /* ── Sections ────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .ft-section {
    padding: 128px 64px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ft-border);
    position: relative;
  }
  .ft-bg-surface { background: var(--ft-surface); }
  .ft-section-content { max-width: 880px; }
  .ft-h2 {
    font-size: 46px;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    max-width: 680px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .ft-section-lead {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--ft-text-dim);
    margin: 0 0 56px;
    max-width: 560px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .ft-two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
  }
  .ft-two-col p {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--ft-text-dim);
    max-width: 420px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Figure (F-Scale) ────────────────────────────────── */
  .ft-figure {
    margin-top: 80px;
    padding: 56px 48px 64px;
